      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Lots of formlines converging but most struggling to find their best. THE BIG FREEZE (6) gets his chance against a moderate line-up. Shade disappointing over a mile last time but fresh for this and back in grade. Has a better record this distance here and gets a chance to bounce back. ANPHINA (5) continues to race well and looks the main danger. Beat THE BIG FREEZE home last time when wound up strongly from well back. Looks tough to hold out again. Both VALLEY PRINCE (3) and DUTY (2) are coming back from 2000m a month ago when safely held in the Figo The Great race. Tough ask for both but suspect this is more suitable trip on both counts. BUADES (4) is coming off a good on-pace second at Tennant Creek latest and off the low draw will be in this for a long way.",
